snippet: Residents of islands from the South Pacific to Australia were alerted to the possibility of a tsunami after an 8.0-magnitude earthquake off the Solomon Islands, but warnings were called off.
abstract: Residents of South Pacific from island chains to Australia are alerted to possibility of tsunami after 8.0-magnitude earthquake strikes off Solomon Islands; warnings are called off hours later as waves dissipate, but not before sending five-foot waves crashing into Santa Cruz Island damaging at least 50 homes..

byline.original: By SUZANNE McFADDEN and GERRY MULLANY

lead_paragraph: Residents of islands from the South Pacific to Australia were alerted to the possibility of a tsunami after an 8.0-magnitude earthquake off the Solomon Islands, but warnings were called off.

headline.seo: Tsunami Fear After Quake Off Solomons
headline.main: Quake Leads to Tsunami, but Fears Ebb
